HEADWORD: Hookes gearing
<hw>Hooke's" gear"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[So called from the
inventor.]</ety> <fld>(Mach.)</fld> <def>Spur gearing having teeth
slanting across the face of the wheel, sometimes slanting in opposite
directions from the middle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hooke's joint</ent>⟦br⟧
